commitResults.messageBody:
Currently there are only methods to delete one specific students, scores
and graded component respectively and it is very inefficient if we want
to delete all the existing data.

As a step to make the codes more efficient, let's implement a command
so that we can clear the existing data efficiently.

Currently, there is no sorting command. As a result, it is hard to
arrange extensive amount of students in order.

Let's implement the sortStu command by alphabetical order of name first.
Allow calculation of scores between classes

Currently SortStudentCommand can only sort the name in alphabetical
order in a decreasing order. As a result, its functionality is very
limited when we need to sort based on other attributes. Let's extend
the functionality by allowing it to sort based on different attributes
and can choose whether to reverse. In addition, let's sort only the
displayed students instead of all students.

commitResults.messageBody:
Currently we can only show all the stats at the same time, however,
this may not be very clear sometime. Let's extend the functionality of
stats command so that it can just show selected stats instead.

Currently the sort command is only for students, however, we may be more
interested in their performance in certain graded components. Let's
implement the sort command for the student scores and show the
associated students in that order.
